To get an overview about the model domain, we first plot the SST during summer.

{% raw %} 
ds_2d = xr.open_dataset("https://thredds-iow.io-warnemuende.de/thredds/dodsC/Persian_Gulf/IOW-THREDDS-Persian_Gulf_PG_SST_reynolds_2020-11-11-11.nc",
decode_times=False)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
ds_2d.isel(time = 0).temp_summer_mod.plot()

<matplotlib.collections.QuadMesh at 0x7f0c267248b0>
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
tef = TEF_object(ds = ds)
{% endraw %}

Note: Calculation will around 3 minutes.

{% raw %} 
tef.calc_flux(-tef.ds.velx3d, tef.ds.hn, tef.ds.dyc)

out1d = tef.sort_1dim(sort_by_variable=tef.ds.salt,
                      flux = tef.flux,
                      N = 100)

out2d = tef.sort_2dim(sort_by_variable=tef.ds.salt,
                      sort_by_variable2=tef.ds.temp,
                      flux = tef.flux,
                      N = 100)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
out2d.q2.mean("time").plot(x = "var_q", y = "var_q2", cmap = plt.cm.RdBu_r)

<matplotlib.collections.QuadMesh at 0x7f68aa1a4d50>
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
f, ax = plt.subplots(1)
plt.plot(out1d.q.mean("time").values, out1d.var_q.values)
ax.invert_yaxis()
ax.set_ylabel("Salinity $[g/kg]$")
